\begin_layout Section
Type of Strategies 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Smallest Continent first
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Popular strategy where the player looks to claim either Australia or South
 America as it is easier to defend due to the limited number of paths into
 and from the continent.
 Easy to build up forces as there are only four territories to maintain
 and the troop bonus is advantageous.
 Places troops on edges of its continents or near continents desired for
 conquering
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Continents First
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Player strategically seeks to claim each continent and doesn’t branch out
 unless a continent can be claimed Defensive playstyle 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Territory First 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Player aims to prevent others from claiming continents by securing territories
 Aggressive playstyle 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Prey on the weak 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Always targets the weakest bordering country When placing, always prefers
 the least-claimed continent Prey on the strong Always attack the owner
 of a continent, if possible, so that no extra points are gained.
 Choose the strongest territory owned by the strongest opponent to attack,
 so long as two dice can still be used.
 
\end_layout

